file descriptors.) The suggested way to handle"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"these cases is to ignore the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You are not supposed to read from the fd yourself, just check for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"readable status. Reading to unset the readable status is done"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"code":"g_cancellable_reset()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in the event that a [signal[Cancellable](\/\/documentation\/gio\/cancellable\/oncancelled(flags:handler:)] signal handler is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"currently running, this call will block until the handler has finished."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Calling this function from a signal handler will therefore result in a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deadlock.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable\/CancellableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a [PollFD](\/\/documentation\/glib\/pollfd corresponding to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":"; this can be passed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"code":"g_poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and used to poll for cancellation. This is useful both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for unix systems without a native poll and for portability to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"windows.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/cancellable\/make(pollfd:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],